# Distillery secrets — env vars (v1).
#
# Keys currently live in the TinyCloud Secret Manager
# (secrets.tinycloud.xyz) and are copied here manually for now.
# Direct vault integration is deferred — headless vault access is blocked
# today (master key needs the root OpenKey passkey signature); see SPEC.md,
# "Future: TinyCloud secrets vault integration".
#
# Gemini key: any ONE of these works (checked in this order, mirroring
# pulse-radio's resolveGeminiKey precedence):
GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# Example local corpus (NEVER hardcoded in skills — transcript paths are
# always passed as invocation arguments):
# "/Users/hunterhorsfall/Obsidian Vaults/TinyCloud 2025/Team Relays/TinyCloud Team Space/Fireflies-Transcripts"

# Comma-separated ABSOLUTE corpus dirs for index-corpus / the feed-run loop.
# The Generate button (POST /api/generate, spec §8) spawns ops/launchd/feedrun.sh,
# which INHERITS the feed server's env — so for the button to run a FULL
# generation the server must be started with TRANSCRIPT_DIRS exported, a Gemini
# key present (above), and `claude` on PATH (the headless agent). A dry_run
# preview needs none of these. ops/launchd/server.env documents the same for the
# keep-alive server; the wrapper also sources ops/launchd/feedrun.env + this .env.
# TRANSCRIPT_DIRS="/abs/Fireflies-Transcripts,/abs/Gemini-Transcripts,/abs/Soundcore-Transcripts"

# --- feed/ OpenKey front-door auth -----------------------------------------
# Comma-separated OpenKey addresses allowed to sign in to the feed
# (case-insensitive compare). The feed gates /api/* and /media/* behind a
# session cookie minted only for these addresses.
OPENKEY_ALLOWED_ADDRESSES=

# Set to 1 to bypass the gate entirely for local HTTP dev (passkeys need a
# secure context, so the OpenKey ceremony can't run over plain http). The
# server logs a loud warning. NEVER set this in production.
# AUTH_DISABLED=1

# Optional override for the session store path (default: feed/sessions.db).
# FEED_SESSIONS_DB=sessions.db
